{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1773483502308,"sessionID":"ses_3142777b4ffe3IuXz7qBZaextx","part":{"id":"prt_cebdaaae3001JwSf5JzENyQWbX","sessionID":"ses_3142777b4ffe3IuXz7qBZaextx","messageID":"msg_cebda9dfe001cMYW3Odaww2Jz3","type":"step-start","snapshot":"cd33686ccf32843707935f75165d83f0fc9b141c"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773483531374,"sessionID":"ses_3142777b4ffe3IuXz7qBZaextx","part":{"id":"prt_cebdaaae4001Wnt5fIImlW15At","sessionID":"ses_3142777b4ffe3IuXz7qBZaextx","messageID":"msg_cebda9dfe001cMYW3Odaww2Jz3","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement token usage display in the wombo-combo TUI. The feature should show token consumption data (input/output tokens, cache, reasoning, cost) across multiple TUI views: Task Browser detail pane, Quest Picker detail pane, a dedicated usage overlay (U keybind), and the wave monitor TUI header.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- Use conventional commits with scope `token-tui` (e.g., `feat(token-tui):`)\n- Commit after each logical unit of work (roughly per subtask)\n- Do NOT push to remote or modify `tasks` directory\n- Run `bun run build` to verify everything works before considering done\n- Token usage data is stored in `.wombo-combo/usage.jsonl` (one JSON record per line, append-only)\n- The `UsageRecord` type has fields: `task_id`, `quest_id`, `model`, `provider`, `input_tokens`, `output_tokens`, `cache_read`, `cache_write`, `reasoning_tokens`, `total_tokens`, `cost`, `is_final_step`, `timestamp`\n- The `token-usage.ts` module provides: `loadUsageRecords()`, `totalUsage()`, `groupBy()`, `filterByDateRange()`, and `UsageStore` class\n- The `token-collector.ts` module provides: `TokenCollector`, `UsageRecord`, `UsageSummary` types\n- The `ProcessMonitor` already has a `tokenCollector` and `usageStore` integrated\n\n## Discoveries\n\n- The codebase uses `neo-blessed` for TUI rendering with tag-based formatting (`{color-fg}text{/color-fg}`)\n- Curly braces in user text must be escaped via `escapeBlessedTags()` to avoid blessed crashes\n- Token usage is already collected by `ProcessMonitor` via `TokenCollector` and persisted to `usage.jsonl` via `UsageStore` - the infrastructure is fully in place, just needs TUI display\n- The `groupBy()` function from `token-usage.ts` groups records by field (`task_id`, `quest_id`, `model`, etc.) and returns `Map<string, UsageTotals>`\n- `UsageTotals` has: `input_tokens`, `output_tokens`, `cache_read`, `cache_write`, `reasoning_tokens`, `total_tokens`, `total_cost`, `record_count`\n- The Task Browser (`tui-browser.ts`) has a detail pane on the right (40% width) showing task metadata\n- The Quest Picker (`tui-quest-picker.ts`) has a detail pane on the right (50% width) showing quest metadata\n- The wave monitor TUI (`tui.ts`) has a header, agent list, preview pane, and status bar\n\n## Accomplished\n\n### Completed:\n1. **Task Browser detail pane token usage** (committed as `028d3fc`): Added per-task token usage display in the Task Browser's detail pane. Shows input/output/cache/reasoning tokens, total tokens, cost, and step count. Data loaded from `usage.jsonl` and grouped by `task_id`. Added helper functions `formatTokenCount()` and `formatCost()` for compact display.\n\n### In Progress:\n2. **Quest Picker per-quest token totals**: Started modifying `tui-quest-picker.ts` - added the imports for `loadUsageRecords`, `totalUsage`, `groupBy` from `token-usage.ts`, and the `UsageTotals` type. Still need to:\n   - Add `questUsage: Map<string, UsageTotals>` field to the `QuestPicker` class\n   - Add `reloadUsage()` method to load and group records by `quest_id`\n   - Call `reloadUsage()` from `loadQuests()`\n   - Add usage display section to `refreshDetail()` method for quest items\n   - Optionally show usage totals in the quest list items\n\n### Not Started:\n3. **Dedicated usage overlay view** (U keybind from Task Browser): Add a blessed overlay showing overall and per-task usage breakdown\n4. **Wave monitor TUI token usage**: Add token usage to the wave monitor header or per-agent display in `tui.ts`\n5. **Final build verification**: Run `bun run build` to verify everything compiles\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n- **`src/lib/tui-browser.ts`** — EDITED. Task Browser TUI view. Added token usage imports, `taskUsage`/`overallUsage` fields, `reloadUsage()` method, `formatTokenCount()`/`formatCost()` helpers, and token usage section in `refreshDetail()`.\n- **`src/lib/tui-quest-picker.ts`** — EDITING (in progress). Quest Picker TUI view. Added imports for token-usage, but still need class fields, data loading, and display logic.\n- **`src/lib/tui.ts`** — READ. Wave monitor TUI. Needs token usage added to header or agent list (not started).\n- **`src/lib/token-usage.ts`** — READ. Persistence and aggregation layer for token usage data. Provides `loadUsageRecords()`, `totalUsage()`, `groupBy()`, `UsageStore`, `UsageTotals`.\n- **`src/lib/token-collector.ts`** — READ. Parsing layer for step_finish events. Provides `TokenCollector`, `UsageRecord`, `UsageSummary`.\n- **`src/lib/monitor.ts`** — READ. Process monitor that integrates `TokenCollector` and `UsageStore`. Already collects and persists usage data.\n- **`src/lib/state.ts`** — READ. Wave state types (`WaveState`, `AgentState`).\n- **`src/lib/tui-session.ts`** — READ. TUI session persistence.\n- **`src/lib/quest-store.ts`** — READ. Quest loading/saving.\n- **`src/lib/quest.ts`** — READ. Quest types.\n- **`AGENTS.md`** — READ. Project conventions.\n- **`package.json`** — READ. Build scripts (`bun run build`).","time":{"start":1773483531373,"end":1773483531373}}}
